{
  "info": {
    "name": "Support & Dispute Service",
    "description": "Local API collection for support-dispute-service (port 8107). API base path: /api/v1/support-disputes.\n\nThe service owns complaints, evidence, disputes, support chat, FAQs and emergency SOS for the customer app and the three provider apps (taxi / dispatch / hauling), plus an admin/back-office surface.\n\nAUTH MODES\n- Public: no auth (categories, FAQs).\n- Customer / Provider: end-user bearer token. Each route group verifies the token with that service's secret and an exact role+service claim match:\n    customer        -> role=customer,        service=customer\n    /provider       -> role=truck_provider,  service=hauling\n    /taxi-provider  -> role=taxi_provider,    service=taxi\n    /dispatch-provider -> role=dispatch_provider, service=dispatch\n  Paste a real access token into {{customer_token}} / {{provider_token}}. (Customers can mint one via customer-service auth: POST /api/v1/customer/auth/start + /verify.)\n- Admin/internal: service-to-service HMAC (shared/go/serviceauth). The 'Admin (HMAC)' folder signs requests automatically via a pre-request script using {{service_name}} / {{service_secret}}. The default service_name (admin-backoffice-service) must match an entry in SUPPORT_DISPUTE_SERVICE_SECRETS.\n\nNotes\n- Provider endpoints are identical to the customer set minus the two dispute routes (dispute escalation is customer-initiated). The 'Provider' folder uses /provider (hauling); swap the prefix for /taxi-provider or /dispatch-provider.\n- The Realtime folder only works when notification-service is running and SUPPORT_DISPUTE_NOTIFICATION_URL is set.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8107" },
    { "key": "api_base", "value": "/api/v1/support-disputes" },
    { "key": "customer_token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "provider_token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "service_name", "value": "admin-backoffice-service" },
    { "key": "service_secret", "value": "development-support-dispute-service-secret" },
    { "key": "complaint_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "dispute_id", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "description": "Liveness probe. Returns 200 once the process is up.",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/health", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["health"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /ready",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "description": "Readiness probe. Returns 200 only when the database is reachable (db.Ping).",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/ready", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["ready"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /meta",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "description": "Service metadata + declared capabilities.",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/meta", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"], "path": ["meta"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Public (no auth)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /support/categories",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "description": "List the complaint category codes (incorrect_delivery, delayed_arrival, payment, damaged_goods, provider_misconduct, fraud, other). Apps render these as a dropdown when filing a complaint.",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/support/categories", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"], "path": ["support", "categories"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /support/faqs",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "description": "Self-service help center. Returns published help_articles filtered by audience. audience = all | customer | provider (omit for 'all').",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/support/faqs?audience=customer",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"],
              "path": ["support", "faqs"],
              "query": [{ "key": "audience", "value": "customer" }]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Customer (bearer)",
      "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{customer_token}}", "type": "string" }] },
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /complaints",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "description": "File a complaint as the authenticated customer. service_type is required (taxi|dispatch|hauling|wallet|platform). category is optional but validated when present. booking_reference ties the complaint to a trip.",
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"service_type\": \"hauling\",\n  \"category\": \"damaged_goods\",\n  \"booking_reference\": \"booking-123\",\n  \"subject\": \"Package arrived damaged\",\n  \"description\": \"The box was crushed on delivery.\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/complaints", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"], "path": ["complaints"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /complaints",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "description": "List my complaints, newest first. Each item includes unread_count for a 'support replied' badge.",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/complaints?limit=50&offset=0",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"],
              "path": ["complaints"],
              "query": [{ "key": "limit", "value": "50" }, { "key": "offset", "value": "0" }]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /complaints/:id",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "description": "View one of my complaints (403 if it is not mine). Includes the live unread message count.",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/complaints/{{complaint_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"], "path": ["complaints", "{{complaint_id}}"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /complaints/:id/evidence",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "description": "Attach evidence (a media URL/asset id from media-file-service + an optional note) to my complaint. Rejected if the complaint is resolved/closed, or if it is not mine (403).",
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"media_url\": \"https://storage.example.com/evidence/photo.jpg\",\n  \"media_asset_id\": \"asset-123\",\n  \"note\": \"Photo of the damaged box\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/complaints/{{complaint_id}}/evidence", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"], "path": ["complaints", "{{complaint_id}}", "evidence"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /complaints/:id/evidence",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "description": "List evidence attached to my complaint (403 if not mine).",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/complaints/{{complaint_id}}/evidence", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"], "path": ["complaints", "{{complaint_id}}", "evidence"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /support-chat/start",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "description": "Open or resume a platform support-chat thread. Returns the (existing or newly created) complaint that backs the chat. Use its id for the messages endpoints.",
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/support-chat/start", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"], "path": ["support-chat", "start"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /complaints/:id/messages",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "description": "Send a chat message on my complaint. The complainant only; admin replies use the admin folder.",
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"content\": \"Hi, any update on my complaint?\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/complaints/{{complaint_id}}/messages", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"], "path": ["complaints", "{{complaint_id}}", "messages"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /complaints/:id/messages",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "description": "Read the chat thread for my complaint (oldest first).",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/complaints/{{complaint_id}}/messages?limit=50&offset=0",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"],
              "path": ["complaints", "{{complaint_id}}", "messages"],
              "query": [{ "key": "limit", "value": "50" }, { "key": "offset", "value": "0" }]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /complaints/:id/messages/read",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "description": "Mark the other party's messages as read (clears the unread badge). Call when the chat screen is opened.",
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/complaints/{{complaint_id}}/messages/read", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"], "path": ["complaints", "{{complaint_id}}", "messages", "read"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /sos",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "description": "Raise an emergency. Creates a priority=emergency complaint with the captured location, acknowledges the reporter, and surfaces at the top of the admin queue. Body is optional.",
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"description\": \"Unsafe situation during my trip\",\n  \"lat\": 6.5244,\n  \"lng\": 3.3792\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/sos", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"], "path": ["sos"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /complaints/:id/dispute (customer only)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "description": "Escalate my complaint into a formal dispute against a respondent. respondent_type must be one of customer|taxi_provider|dispatch_provider|hauling_provider. Marks the complaint 'escalated'.",
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"respondent_type\": \"hauling_provider\",\n  \"respondent_id\": \"provider-123\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/complaints/{{complaint_id}}/dispute", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"], "path": ["complaints", "{{complaint_id}}", "dispute"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /complaints/:id/dispute (customer only)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "description": "View the dispute raised on my complaint (403 if not mine).",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}{{api_base}}/complaints/{{complaint_id}}/dispute", "host": ["{{base_url}}{{api_base}}"], "path": ["complaints", "{{complaint_id}}", "dispute"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
